name: Dot

outputs.name: Result
outputs.description: The result of the dot product

description:
Calculate the dot product between two vectors. For example, the dot product of vector A [1, -3, -2] and B [5, -1, 1] is:
[1, -3, -2] Â· [5, -1, 1] = (1 x 5) + (-3 x -1) + (-2 x 1) = 6
Supported types: Vec2, Vec3, and Vec4.
